<div type="addressee"><ab facs="#facs_92_r1l9">Den von Vlme </ab>
</div>
<!-- This div contains the letter itselfs. Additions to the text are contained in <add/> elements, struck text in <hi> elements with the attribute 'strikethrough' set to true. -->
<div type="content"><ab facs="#facs_92_r1l11"><expan>L<ex>ieben</ex></expan> <expan>fr<ex>ewnde</ex></expan> als Jr vns 
<add><ab facs="#facs_92_r1l10">nehſt </ab></add> <expan>verſchr<ex>iben</ex></expan> vnd <expan>gebette<ex>n</ex></expan> habt eẅch ein <expan>abſchr<ex>ift</ex></expan> der <expan>freıh<ex>eit</ex></expan> </ab>
<ab facs="#facs_92_r1l12">als <expan>vnſ<ex>er</ex></expan> <expan>gnedıgſt<ex>er</ex></expan> <expan>h<ex>er</ex>re</expan> ~ der Römıſch künıg . der Jüdıſcheıt bey vns wonent </ab>
<ab facs="#facs_92_r1l13"><expan>gegeb<ex>e</ex>n</expan> hat / ʒu ſchıken etc das <expan>hab<ex>e</ex>n</expan> wır wol <expan>v<ex>er</ex>nom<ex>en</ex></expan> Vnd wır <expan>well<ex>e</ex>n</expan> das </ab>
<ab facs="#facs_92_r1l14"><expan>eẅr<ex>er</ex></expan> <expan>weıſh<ex>eit</ex></expan> ʒu lıeb <expan>g<ex>er</ex>n</expan> tun Vnd <expan>ſchık<ex>en</ex></expan> eẅch <expan>derſelb<ex>e</ex>n</expan> <expan>freıh<ex>eit</ex></expan> ein <expan>abſchr<ex>ift</ex></expan> </ab>
<ab facs="#facs_92_r1l15">in dıſem <expan>vnſ<ex>er</ex>m</expan> brıef <expan>v<ex>er</ex>ſloſſen</expan> . Denn wo wır <expan>ewr<ex>er</ex></expan> <expan>erſamk<ex>eit</ex></expan> etc </ab>
<ab facs="#facs_92_r1l17"><expan>Dat<ex>um</ex></expan> vt <expan>ſ<ex>upra</ex></expan> </ab>
</div>
</div><div type="regularised"><pb facs="#facs_92" id="46r"/><!--The following div is the container for the adress lines of the letter.-->
<div type="addressee">
<ab>Den von Ulme </ab>
</div>
<!-- This div contains the letter itselfs. Additions to the text are contained in <add/> elements, struck text in <hi> elements with the attribute 'strikethrough' set to true. -->
<div type="content">
<ab><expan>L<ex>ieben</ex></expan>
<expan>fr<ex>eunde,</ex></expan> als ir uns <add>nehst</add>
<expan>verschr<ex>iben</ex></expan> und <expan>gebette<ex>n</ex></expan>
                        habt, ewch ein <expan>abschr<ex>ift</ex></expan> der
                                <expan>freih<ex>eit</ex></expan>, als <expan>uns<ex>er</ex></expan>
<expan>gnedigst<ex>er</ex></expan>
<expan>h<ex>er</ex>re,</expan> der römisch künig, der jüdischeit bey uns
                        wonent <expan>gegeb<ex>e</ex>n</expan> hat, zu schiken etc., das
                                <expan>hab<ex>e</ex>n</expan> wir wol
                                <expan>v<ex>er</ex>nom<ex>en</ex></expan>. Und wir
                                <expan>well<ex>e</ex>n</expan> das <expan>ewr<ex>er</ex></expan>
<expan>weish<ex>eit</ex></expan> zu lieb <expan>g<ex>er</ex>n</expan> tun
                        und <expan>schik<ex>en</ex></expan> ewch <expan>derselb<ex>e</ex>n</expan>
<expan>freih<ex>eit</ex></expan> ein <expan>abschr<ex>ift</ex></expan> in
                        disem <expan>uns<ex>er</ex>m</expan> brief
                            <expan>v<ex>er</ex>slossen</expan>. Denn wo wir
                            <expan>ewr<ex>er</ex></expan>
<expan>ersamk<ex>eit</ex></expan> etc. <expan>Dat<ex>um</ex></expan> ut
                                <expan>s<ex>upra.</ex></expan>
</ab>
</div>
